\b\fs24 Playing Solitaire by Using the Keyboard\plain\fs24 
\par \pard\sb115\sl235\li115\ri175 \fs20 If you don't have a mouse, use the following keys to play Solitaire.
\par \trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-101 \cellx1454\cellx3874\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \b\ul Press\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 To\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-101 \cellx1454\cellx3874\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs16 TAB\fs20 \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 Move among the deck, suit stacks, and row stacks. \fs16 TAB\fs20  selects a stack only if that stack is applicable to the next move.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-101 \cellx1454\cellx3874\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \fs16 LEFT\fs20  and \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20 \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 Move to the next stack.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-101 \cellx1454\cellx3874\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \fs16 UP\fs20  and \fs16 DOWN ARROW\fs20 \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 Move from card to card within the stack.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-101 \cellx1454\cellx3874\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 Pick up and release a card or group of cards. \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20  also turns over a new card in the deck or a stack, and "turns over" the deck itself.\cell\intbl\row
