Playing the Game\plain\fs24 
\par \pard\sb115\sl235\li115\ri175 \fs20 The object of Solitaire is to use all the cards in the deck to build up the four suit stacks from Ace to King. Playing Solitaire involves the following procedures. 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To move a card by using a mouse
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab From the deck or a stack, drag the card to where you want it, and then release the mouse button. 
\par \tab Or, to move more than one card from a stack, drag the uppermost card you want to move, and then release the mouse button where you want to place the cards. 
\par \tab You can also move a card from a row stack to a suit stack by double-clicking the card. 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To move a card by using the keyboard
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 1.\tab Use \fs16 TAB\fs20  to move to the deck or stack. 
\par 2.\tab Use the \fs16 LEFT\fs20  or \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20  key to select the card, and then press \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 . 
\par \tab Or, to move more than one card from a stack, use the \fs16 LEFT\fs20  or \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20  key to move to the stack, and then use the \fs16 UP ARROW\fs20  key to select the uppermost card you want to move. Then press \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or the \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 . 
\par 3.\tab If you are moving a card from the deck, press \fs16 TAB\fs20  to quickly move the card to the suit or row stacks. 
\par \pard\sb55\sa115\sl235\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \tab Use the \fs16 LEFT\fs20  or \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20  key to move the card(s) to the stack you want, and then press \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or the \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 . 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To cancel your last move
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\sl235\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab From the Game menu, choose Undo. 
\par \pard\sb115\sl235\li115\ri175 You can undo the last card moved or the last card drawn from the deck. 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To turn over a card in a stack or in the deck
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab Click the face-down card. 
\par \tab Or use the \fs16 TAB\fs20  and \fs16 LEFT\fs20  or \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20  keys to select the stack or deck, and then press \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or the \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 . 
\par \tab Solitaire turns over one or three cards in a deck, depending on whether you select the Draw One or Draw Three option before the game is dealt. 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To turn over the deck
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab Click to the left of the deck to turn it over, and then continue drawing cards. 
\par \tab Or use the \fs16 LEFT\fs20  or \fs16 RIGHT ARROW\fs20  key to select the space to the left of the deck, and then press \fs16 ENTER\fs20  or the \fs16 SPACEBAR\fs20 . 
\par \tab If you are using Standard scoring, you lose 20 points for each pass through the deck after three passes (Draw Three option), or 100 points for each pass through the deck after one pass (Draw One option). 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To pause a game
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab Click the Minimize button. 
\par \tab Or, from the Control menu, choose Minimize. 
\par \tab Timing stops when the game is paused. 
\par \tab To resume the game, double-click the Solitaire icon at the bottom of the desktop. 
\par \tab Or, if you are using the keyboard, select the Solitaire icon at the bottom of the desktop, and then choose Restore from the Control menu. 
\par \pard\sb115\sa25\sl235\li115\ri175 \b To start a new game
\par \pard\sb115\sa55\li395\ri175\fi-275\tx395 \plain\fs20 \{bmc bm2.BMP\}\tab From the Game menu, choose Deal. 
