Setting Game Options\plain\fs24 
\par \pard\sb115\sl235\li115\ri175 \fs20 You can use several options when playing Solitaire by choosing the Options command from the Game menu. 
\par You can use Draw options to specify how many cards to turn over in the deck. The Draw One option turns over the top card. The Draw Three option turns over three cards. 
\par Scoring options include Standard and Vegas. You can also turn scoring off. 
\par Display options include the following:
\par \trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-100 \cellx1324\cellx3634\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \b\ul Use\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 To\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-100 \cellx1324\cellx3634\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Timed Game\b\ul \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Keep track of the time elapsed during a game.\b\ul \cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-100 \cellx1324\cellx3634\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Status Bar\b\ul \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Display the status bar at the bottom of the Solitaire window to show your score and time.\b\ul \cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-100 \cellx1324\cellx3634\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Keep Score\b\ul \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Keep a running total of your score from game to game when using Vegas scoring.\b\ul \cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trqc\trgaph109\trleft-100 \cellx1324\cellx3634\pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Outline Dragging\b\ul \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb115\sl235\li115 \plain\fs20 Display an outline of the card being moved, and change the color of the space or card you are moving to (if the move is valid).\b\ul \cell\intbl\row
